{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Product Spec\n\n## Research Evidence\n- Evidence inputs reviewed: App Store reviews, Reddit pain mining, competitor scans, iOS design-pattern synthesis, and the quality bar contract.\n- Evidence confidence: medium-high. Signals are consistent across sources on reliability distrust, anti-autopilot need, ad friction, and relapse after dismissal.\n- Primary target user: heavy sleepers and chronic snoozers facing real-world consequences (work, school, caregiving, shift transitions).\n- Core job-to-be-done: convert `alarm fired` into `awake and executing first morning action`, not just dismissal.\n\n## User Journeys\n- `J-01 Critical Wake`: User creates a strict alarm with mission stack, alarm fires, user completes adaptive mission, passes wake-check, completes first micro-task, and sees reliability timeline entry.\n- `J-02 Relapse Recovery`: User dismisses but ignores wake-check; app escalates (configured louder pattern / repeat challenge), requires re-validation, logs escalation outcome.\n- `J-03 Trust Verification`: User opens reliability ledger and sees per-alarm timeline: scheduled, triggered, mission completion, wake-check status, escalation/failure reason.\n- `J-04 Fast Setup`: New user completes setup wizard with iOS constraint disclosure, permission rationale, and privacy explanation before first alarm activation.\n\n## MVP Scope\n- In scope:\n  - Alarm creation/editing with mission stack and strictness level.\n  - Adaptive mission rotation across at least 3 modalities: cognitive, movement, scan/photo/object.\n  - Post-dismiss wake-check contract with configurable window and escalation.\n  - Reliability ledger with human-readable per-alarm execution logs.\n  - First-task bridge: one user-selected micro-task required after wake verification.\n  - Ad-free critical wake path (active alarm + immediate post-dismiss + wake-check).\n  - Basic weekly wake consistency summary.\n- Non-goals:\n  - Sleep-stage tracking platform.\n  - Public social feed or stranger accountability mechanics.\n  - Wellness content library (stories/sounds/coaching).\n  - Wearable-dependent launch requirements.\n\n## Boilerplate Reuse\n- Base: extend `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` in `apps/waketask-iphone`; no platform rebuild.\n- Mandatory policy: extend before replace.\n- Rebuilds forbidden without ADR-level justification: auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, design system, DI/composition root.\n- Any proposed net-new infrastructure must include:\n  - Existing module evaluated.\n  - Gap found.\n  - Why extension is not viable.\n  - Replacement cost/benefit and App Store 4.3 impact.\n\n## Design Direction\n- Product tone: calm, serious, high-trust; avoid gimmick and shame framing.\n- UX priorities:\n  - Single clear next action during active alarm.\n  - Large controls, high legibility, high contrast, clear countdown/status.\n  - No monetization interruptions in critical wake path.\n  - Explicit privacy copy for on-device mission validation.\n- Differentiation Contract (4.3 hardening):\n  - `D-01` Reliability ledger is visible and usable in first session.\n  - `D-02` Post-dismiss wake-check escalation is active and configurable.\n  - `D-03` Adaptive anti-autopilot mission rotation changes mission pattern over time.\n  - `D-04` First-task bridge is integrated into wake completion flow.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `FR-01 Alarm Setup`: User can create, edit, enable, disable alarms with mission stack and strictness.\n  - Verification: UI test creates and edits alarm; persisted state reload confirms values.\n- `FR-02 Mission Engine`: App supports at least 3 mission modalities and rotation logic.\n  - Verification: unit tests validate modality selection and anti-repeat rules.\n- `FR-03 Wake Contract`: Dismissal requires wake-check within configured window; missed check triggers escalation.\n  - Verification: integration test with mocked time path asserts escalation state transition.\n- `FR-04 Reliability Ledger`: Each alarm run writes timeline records with success/failure reason.\n  - Verification: repository integration test asserts schema fields and ordering.\n- `FR-05 First-Task Bridge`: Wake flow is incomplete until selected micro-task marked complete.\n  - Verification: UI test blocks completion until first task done.\n- `FR-06 Ad-Free Critical Path`: No interstitial ads in alarm, dismiss, wake-check flows.\n  - Verification: release audit checklist plus automated string scan for ad-sdk entrypoints in critical flow module.\n- `NFR-01 Performance`: cold launch p95 <= 2.0s on target simulator profile.\n  - Verification: startup metric capture in CI report.\n- `NFR-02 Interaction Latency`: mission interaction response p95 <= 200ms.\n  - Verification: UI performance test with 30 sampled actions.\n- `NFR-03 Stability`: crash-free sessions >= 99.5% in pre-release test runs.\n  - Verification: Appium exploratory + XCTest run logs with crash count = 0 for gate pass.\n- `NFR-04 Accessibility`: Dynamic Type, VoiceOver labels, contrast >= WCAG AA, tap targets >= 44x44 pt for core flows.\n  - Verification: accessibility audit checklist + XCTest assertions where automatable.\n- `NFR-05 Privacy/Data`: mission validation data processed on-device for MVP; no secret values logged.\n  - Verification: code review plus log scan gate with zero violations.\n- `NFR-06 File/Code Quality`: Swift production and test files remain <= 400 lines; Swift 6 strict concurrency preserved.\n  - Verification: lint/build gate and line-count script in CI.\n\n## Appium Exploratory QA\n- Required artifact: `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`.\n- Pass conditions:\n  - Real simulator/Appium/XCUITest run executed.\n  - `buttons_tapped > 0` and representative coverage of all reachable MVP screens.\n  - `crashes = 0`, `failures = 0`.\n- Required report fields:\n  - `ok`, `buttons_tapped`, `screens_visited`, `crashes`, `failures`, `failures_detail`.\n- Deferral policy:\n  - Deferral allowed only when explicit workflow input sets `defer_appium: true` and a blocking simulator issue is documented in evidence.\n  - Without both conditions, release is blocked.\n\n## App Store Readiness\n- 4.3 anti-clone gate must pass:\n  - Differentiation contract (`D-01`..`D-04`) is visible in onboarding, core wake flow, and metadata/screenshots narrative.\n  - Release strings and metadata must not read as generic template alarm clone copy.\n- Compliance and release evidence must include:\n  - `xcodebuild build` pass.\n  - `xcodebuild test` pass.\n  - SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, and secret scan all pass as blocking gates.\n  - Privacy disclosures align with actual data behavior.\n- Security handling:\n  - Credential checks are true/false presence only.\n  - No printing/logging/writing of secret values in artifacts.\n\n## Definition of Done\n- Canonical DoD is maintained in `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md` and is release-blocking.\n- `Done` requires every checklist item to be verifiably satisfied with evidence artifacts.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
